00:57.474 --> 01:01.061
<i>I saw </i>48 Hrs.
<i>at a local multiplex in December, 1982,</i>

01:01.144 --> 01:02.312
<i>when I was nine years old.</i>

01:03.063 --> 01:06.691
<i>My parents dropped me and a buddy off,</i>
<i>and as was the custom,</i>

01:06.775 --> 01:09.319
<i>we snuck into it</i>
<i>after buying tickets for something else.</i>

01:10.153 --> 01:13.698
<i>It was the talk of the third grade,</i>
<i>and seeing it was a rite of passage.</i>

01:15.408 --> 01:18.787
48 Hrs. <i>was developed</i>
<i>at Michael Eisner's Paramount Pictures,</i>

01:18.870 --> 01:21.539
<i>hardly the gold standard</i>
<i>for socially challenging fare.</i>

01:22.290 --> 01:24.334
<i>It was meant to be</i>
<i>a conventional action comedy</i>

01:24.417 --> 01:27.212
<i>and expedient bit</i>
<i>of holiday counter-programming.</i>

01:27.587 --> 01:30.131
<i>But somehow,</i>
<i>director Walter Hill's film</i>

01:30.215 --> 01:34.010
<i>landed in theaters as this edgy,</i>
<i>even dangerous, conversation</i>

01:34.094 --> 01:36.554
<i>about race and identity in America.</i>

01:36.638 --> 01:39.057
<i>It was a conversation I was ready for.</i>

01:39.557 --> 01:41.643
<i>A conversation about us.</i>

01:41.726 --> 01:44.145
<i>A conversation about you and me.</i>

01:45.063 --> 01:46.731
<i>It was the best movie I'd ever seen.</i>

01:46.815 --> 01:47.774
Police. Open up.

01:47.857 --> 01:51.569
<i>An entry into a forbidden world</i>
<i>of the profane and the violent,</i>

01:51.653 --> 01:53.780
<i>and I didn't understand</i>
<i>even a little bit of it.</i>

01:54.405 --> 01:55.657
<i>But I knew Reggie.</i>

01:56.032 --> 01:58.284
<i>I recognized the defense mechanisms</i>
<i>he'd developed</i>

01:58.368 --> 02:01.079
<i>in coping with the racism</i>
<i>of his day-to-day</i>

02:01.162 --> 02:02.956
<i>as ones I was beginning to develop.</i>

02:03.456 --> 02:07.127
<i>And as the only Chinese kid</i>
<i>in an all-white area of Colorado…</i>

02:07.877 --> 02:09.295
<i>I knew guys like Jack too.</i>

02:10.588 --> 02:13.842
You are real stupid for a cop, man.
You're following this guy too close.

02:13.925 --> 02:15.385
