You know where to find him?

12:31.208 --> 12:33.961
I don't give a shit what the fuck
your badge says, nigger.

12:34.044 --> 12:37.423
<i>It's all based on an African-American man</i>
<i>assaulting an entire bar</i>…

12:38.090 --> 12:40.176
<i>full of racist, redneck idiots.</i>

12:40.968 --> 12:45.514
<i>In an action movie filled with exciting</i>
<i>set pieces, this is the showstopper.</i>

12:45.598 --> 12:48.100
<i>Set in a caricature</i>
<i>of regressive whiteness</i>

12:48.184 --> 12:51.520
<i>dropped in the middle</i>
<i>of the most progressive city in America,</i>

12:51.604 --> 12:54.648
48 Hrs. <i>is many things,</i>
<i>but it's about race.</i>

12:55.191 --> 12:57.860
-I don't like white people.
-<i>It's worth stating again…</i>

12:57.943 --> 12:59.528
That means I'm enjoying this shit.

12:59.612 --> 13:02.948
<i>…this is Eddie Murphy</i>
<i>in his very first screen performance.</i>

13:03.032 --> 13:04.074


13:04.158 --> 13:07.787
Oh this is so fabulous. Ain't nothin' like
having a good meal with family.

13:07.870 --> 13:09.789
<i>Younger audiences may only know Murphy</i>

13:09.872 --> 13:12.666
<i>as a shape-shifting,</i>
<i>family-friendly performer.</i>

13:12.750 --> 13:15.127
<i>In fact, Murphy himself</i>
<i>has long driven the narrative</i>

13:15.211 --> 13:18.005
<i>of being a Black performer</i>
<i>white America can agree on.</i>

13:18.756 --> 13:20.800
<i>He's not Black or white. He's Eddie.</i>

13:21.300 --> 13:23.260
<i>But if you backtrack through </i>Shrek…

13:23.344 --> 13:24.637
You cut me deep, Shrek.

13:24.720 --> 13:26.639
-…<i>Dr. Dolittle</i>…
-Come on!

13:26.722 --> 13:30.059
…<i>Mulan, The Nutty Professor</i>
and <i>Coming to America</i>…

13:30.142 --> 13:32.311
Halt! When you think of garbage,
think of Akeem.

13:32.394 --> 13:34.563
<i>…you get back to the sharp edges of films</i>

13:34.647 --> 13:37.733
<i>like </i>Beverly Hills Cop, Trading Places…

13:37.817 --> 13:41.487
-You don't know who you're messing with!
-May I suggest using your nightstick?

13:41.570 --> 13:43.280
<i>…and especially </i>48 Hrs.

13:44.031 --> 13:47.952
<i>Before the movies, he was a young stand-up</i>
<i>known for his blue routines</i>

13:48.035 --> 13:51.997
<i>and building heat as the first Black</i>
<i>breakout star of </i>Saturday Night Live.

13:52.081 --> 13:55.000
This is how you answer a door
in my neighborhood.

13:55.960 --> 13:56.794
Who is it?

13:57.795 --> 13:59.129
<i>He idolized Richard Pryor,</i>

13:59.213 --> 14:03.092
<i>who also talked dirty and influenced</i>
<i>people with sharp, polarizing material.</i>

14:03.175 --> 14:06.220
'Cause if you're in an argument
with another man, he may be white,

14:06.303 --> 14:08.639
but it's man-on-man for a minute,
and the shit get rough,

14:08.722 --> 14:10.516
he end up calling you "Nigger!"

14:11.016 --> 14:15.229
You gotta go, "Oh, shit.
Now, I ain't no man no more."

14:15.312 --> 14:20.025
<i>Which, like Eddie, led to edgy, socially</i>
<i>responsible films such as </i>Blue Collar…

14:20.109 --> 14:24.071
Everybody know what the plant is.
The "plant" just short for "plantation."

14:24.154 --> 14:24.989
Right on!

14:25.072 --> 14:27.658
<i>…before similarly ending up</i>
<i>in humiliating product</i>

14:27.741 --> 14:30.995
<i>as literally a toy for a rich white kid.</i>

14:31.662 --> 14:32.872
<i>I wonder if it's the price</i>

14:32.955 --> 14:36.375
<i>of any kind of real success</i>
<i>in the United States for minorities.</i>

14:36.458 --> 14:39.336
<i>Dial back the angry to keep the men</i>
<i>signing the checks happy.</i>

14:40.170 --> 14:44.675
<i>But in the scene at Torchy's, Eddie Murphy</i>
<i>is still at his most dangerous.</i>

14:44.758 --> 14:46.343
What the hell kind of cop are you?

14:47.344 --> 14:50.055
You know what I am?
I'm your worst fucking nightmare, man.

14:50.139 --> 14:53.934
A nigger with a badge. I got permission
to kick your fucking ass whenever I want.

14:54.018 --> 14:55.185
<i>And in this moment,</i>

14:55.269 --> 14:58.063
<i>he became the most important</i>
<i>Black actor since Sidney Poitier…</i>

14:58.647 --> 15:01.358
<i>and for many of the same</i>
<i>norm-shattering reasons.</i>

15:01.442 --> 15:03.944
-Where the fuck did you get this?
-Tax refund.

15:04.028 --> 15:06.864
Bullshit. You're too fucking stupid
to have a job.

15:06.947 --> 15:09.074
<i>He's an existential threat</i>
<i>to the ruling order</i>

15:09.158 --> 15:11.785
<i>in a way he arguably never will be again,</i>

15:11.869 --> 15:13.996
<i>not to this extent, on screen.</i>

15:14.622 --> 15:19.627
<i>Hill and Murphy are invested in discussing</i>
<i>race in ways that are frank, unadorned.</i>

15:20.669 --> 15:23.172
<i>Profane and profound.</i>

15:23.255 --> 15:26.216
<i>He's representative</i>
<i>of a threatening kind of Blackness.</i>

15:26.634 --> 15:30.804
<i>The kind that is aware of the tactics of</i>
<i>the white ruling class that hate his guts.</i>

15:30.888 --> 15:32.056
There's a new sheriff in town.

15:32.681 --> 15:35.935
<i>And he uses it</i>
<i>as his righteous sword and shield.</i>

15:37.186 --> 15:40.814
And his name is Reggie Hammond.
Y'all be cool. Right on.

15:43.442 --> 15:45.361
<i>Reggie has assumed Jack's power.</i>

15:45.444 --> 15:48.405
<i>And for that transgression,</i>
<i>Jack must reassert his.</i>

15:48.489 --> 15:50.532
I want to know
what the fuck this is all about.

15:50.616 --> 15:52.576
Maybe I don't like the way you asked me,
all right?

15:52.660 --> 15:55.704
Who gives a goddamn what you like?
You're just a spearchucker

15:55.788 --> 15:58.874
with a number stenciled
on the back of his prison fatigues.

15:59.375 --> 16:02.252
<i>They get into a fistfight,</i>
<i>and it must be said</i>

16:02.336 --> 16:05.339
<i>that there are few directors</i>
<i>who tell character better through action</i>

16:05.422 --> 16:06.590
<i>than Walter Hill.</i>

16:07.132 --> 16:09.218
<i>Their fighting styles are different.</i>

16:09.301 --> 16:11.136
<i>Jack's is wild and ungainly.</i>

16:12.554 --> 16:14.598
<i>Reggie's, is staccato and sharp.</i>

16:15.641 --> 16:17.142
<i>Reggie keeps his cool throughout…</i>

16:17.226 --> 16:18.310
You little fucker.

16:18.394 --> 16:20.938
<i>…until Jack throws him</i>
<i>on a pile of garbage.</i>

16:21.021 --> 16:22.898
You pushed me in the fucking garbage?

16:23.399 --> 16:26.485
<i>He recognizes the gesture</i>
<i>as condescending.</i>

16:26.568 --> 16:28.904
<i>A line has been crossed.</i>

16:28.988 --> 16:31.240
<i>It's outside the normal race-baiting.</i>

16:31.991 --> 16:35.786
<i>Reggie will not be demeaned</i>
<i>during the course of this 48 hours.</i>

16:42.001 --> 16:43.919
They saved your ass, convict.

16:44.586 --> 16:46.672
That's what you tell 'em
at the station house.

16:46.755 --> 16:50.050
Yeah, right.
I'll even put it in my report that way.

16:50.968 --> 16:52.136
Yeah, I bet you will.

16:52.219 --> 16:53.429
<i>When Jack tells Reggie</i>

16:53.512 --> 16:55.848
<i>that he's going to put in his report</i>
<i>that he won the fight,</i>

16:55.931 --> 16:58.434
<i>it's an acknowledgment</i>
<i>that though Jack has lost,</i>

16:58.517 --> 17:01.562
<i>he has the institutional power</i>
<i>to control the narrative.</i>

17:01.979 --> 17:02.896
Right, partner.

17:03.397 --> 17:07.026
<i>But one of the marvels of Murphy's</i>
<i>performance is his ability throughout</i>

17:07.109 --> 17:10.696
<i>to imbue Reggie with,</i>
<i>of all things, dignity.</i>

17:10.779 --> 17:15.117
Get this, man. We ain't brothers,
we ain't partners, and we ain't friends.

17:15.200 --> 17:17.911
If Ganz gets away with my money,
you'll be sorry you ever met me.

17:18.454 --> 17:20.122
<i>I have aspired all my life</i>

17:20.205 --> 17:24.043
<i>to have Reggie's confidence and dignity</i>
<i>in my own racial identity.</i>

17:31.467 --> 17:35.054
<i>Later, in Vroman's,</i>
<i>the exact mirror opposite of Torchy's,</i>

17:35.137 --> 17:38.265
<i>the pivotal scene in the movie</i>
<i>occurs as Reggie is in his element.</i>

17:38.348 --> 17:41.143
Vodka with a twist,
and I'd like to run up a tab, please.

17:41.226 --> 17:43.854
<i> You can tell,</i>
<i>because he's allowed to open a tab,</i>

17:43.937 --> 17:47.941
<i>and Hill, in another hallmark, gives</i>
<i>the band plenty of time to do their thing.</i>

17:48.025 --> 17:49.985
Hammond, where the hell are you?

17:50.069 --> 17:51.487
Vroman's in the Fillmore.

17:52.571 --> 17:55.866
Yeah, I know you don't know about
this place. The brothers hang out here.

17:56.366 --> 17:59.995
48 Hrs., <i>already an impeccable,</i>
<i>lean vehicle…</i>

18:00.537 --> 18:03.999
<i>in this moment becomes something</i>
<i>very much like an important film.</i>

18:05.709 --> 18:10.089
<i>At this moment, it doesn't matter what</i>
48 Hrs. <i>set out to be. At this moment…</i>

18:10.172 --> 18:11.215
Hammond!

18:11.298 --> 18:14.093
<i>…for an ostracized kid</i>
<i>looking to make sense of the senseless…</i>

18:14.176 --> 18:15.761
-Candy, this is Jack.
Hello.

18:15.844 --> 18:16.720
And goodbye.

18:17.221 --> 18:19.807
<i>…</i>48 Hrs. <i>is truly great.</i>

18:20.599 --> 18:21.767
<i>Jack apologizes.</i>

18:25.312 --> 18:28.023
"Nigger" and "watermelon,"
I didn't mean that stuff.

18:28.816 --> 18:31.068
I was just doing my job, keeping you down.

18:32.861 --> 18:35.781
Yeah, well, "doing your job"
don't explain everything, Jack.

18:36.323 --> 18:37.449
Yeah, you're right.

18:37.533 --> 18:39.868
<i>And Reggie tells him,</i>
<i>in an almost offhand way…</i>

18:40.869 --> 18:42.955
<i>…that Jack is not, in fact, forgiven.</i>

18:44.998 --> 18:47.835
<i>Even as a nine-year-old kid,</i>
<i>I recognized the grace</i>

18:47.918 --> 18:52.256
<i>of this practiced, measured dismissal</i>
<i>of a buddy's blindness to my pain,</i>

18:52.339 --> 18:53.549
<i>and the lengths I would go</i>

18:53.632 --> 18:57.010
<i>to make these uncomfortable moments</i>
<i>as invisible as I felt.</i>

18:58.512 --> 19:02.933
<i>When I first saw this film, I was too</i>
<i>young to unpack all of my reactions to it,</i>

19:03.016 --> 19:04.351
<i>much less begin to unravel</i>

19:04.434 --> 19:07.646
<i>the riddle of race and representation</i>
<i>in the United States.</i>

19:08.188 --> 19:10.440
<i>I'm not sure</i>
<i>it's a knot we'll ever fully untangle.</i>

19:10.524 --> 19:12.651
I got five deaths related to Ganz,

19:12.734 --> 19:15.445
and you blow it
for a lousy nigger convict!

19:16.238 --> 19:18.949
That's right! I called him a nigger!
You bet I did!

19:19.032 --> 19:21.535
<i>There's no hugging it out</i>
<i>between Jack and Reggie…</i>

19:22.035 --> 19:25.122
<i>but there is devastating indictment</i>
<i>of how white and Black Americans</i>

19:25.205 --> 19:28.167
<i>circle around</i>
<i>these hyper-charged racial divides</i>

19:28.250 --> 19:32.129
<i>that are embedded in our country</i>
<i>without ever bridging that chasm.</i>

19:32.212 --> 19:36.300
Now wait a minute, goddamn it! I'm gonna
tell you something about this man.

19:36.383 --> 19:41.180
He has more brains than you'll ever know.
Got more guts than any partner I ever had.

19:41.263 --> 19:43.640
You go fuck yourself, convict!

19:44.725 --> 19:46.018
<i>At the end of it all,</i>

19:46.101 --> 19:49.021
<i>Jack goes back to his corner</i>
<i>and Reggie goes back to jail.</i>

19:49.104 --> 19:51.481
Wait a minute.
Ganz got away with all my money,

19:51.565 --> 19:53.734
and you gonna take me back to jail
in my own car.

19:54.776 --> 19:56.486
Somehow, this shit don't seem right.

19:56.987 --> 19:59.323
Yeah, a lot of things don't seem right.

19:59.406 --> 20:02.743
<i>They aren't friends, but they are closer</i>
<i>to what Ganz and Billy Bear were</i>

20:02.826 --> 20:04.536
<i>at the beginning of </i>48 Hrs.

20:04.620 --> 20:06.496
<i>Co-conspirators in a crime.</i>

20:07.122 --> 20:09.166
<i>Maybe that's as close as we ever get.</i>

20:09.917 --> 20:13.128
<i>When Reggie and Jack make a deal</i>
<i>about the money that Reggie's stolen…</i>

20:13.212 --> 20:14.630
This what you wanna talk about?

20:14.713 --> 20:18.926
<i>…it's predicated on trust, and there's</i>
<i>a feeling, confirmed by the sequel…</i>

20:19.009 --> 20:21.887
It's your money. It'll be there
in six months when you get out.

20:21.970 --> 20:23.805
<i>…that Jack's not to be trusted.</i>

20:23.889 --> 20:26.183
I'm gonna be an honest man
from now on, right?

20:27.809 --> 20:29.686
<i>Reggie isn't to be trusted either.</i>

20:29.770 --> 20:31.355
Can I have my lighter back, Reggie?

20:35.067 --> 20:38.403
48 Hrs. <i>isn't a buddy comedy,</i>
<i>because they're not buddies.</i>

20:39.154 --> 20:41.990
<i>And more than not being a comedy,</i>
<i>it's a tragedy</i>

20:42.074 --> 20:46.245
<i>in which whatever brotherhood discovered</i>
<i>by these men is abandoned at the end</i>

20:46.328 --> 20:48.830
<i>by the circumstances</i>
<i>of our shared reality.</i>

20:49.831 --> 20:51.792
<i>Maybe it's the great American tragedy…</i>

20:52.459 --> 20:55.128
<i>that however long</i>
<i>we spend in one another's company,</i>

20:55.212 --> 20:57.881
<i>I will only ever be one thing</i>
<i>in your eyes…</i>

20:58.257 --> 21:01.051
<i>and you will only ever be</i>
<i>the thing who doesn't see me.</i>

22:21.298 --> 22:26.636
